{"title":"AASQ Callout: Ask WTB how to find your best tire pressure for gravel and MTB!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/17/aasq-callout-ask-wtb-how-to-find-your-best-tire-pressure-for-gravel-and-mtb/","date":1615991809000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>Next week, we have gravel and mountain bike tire experts WTB at <em>your</em> disposal. Clayton Wangbichler and James Heaton are on hand to answer your questions on the topic of tire pressure.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/AASQ-submit-button.gif\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%22%20width%3D%22300%22%20height%3D%2250%22%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E\" alt=\"button to submit questions for bikerumor AASQ series\" width=\"300\" height=\"50\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/AASQ-submit-button.gif\"></a></p><p>Many riders aren’t fussy about their tire pressure. When you ask them trail side what pressures they are running, some simply respond with “some”, often with an I-couldn’t-care-less-expression upon their face.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62.jpg\" alt=\"WTB RADDLER GRAVEL TIRE PRESSURE\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/2020_WTB_Raddler_JS-62-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Others are quite the opposite, checking their tire pressure before every single ride, adjusting it to the conditions and a bunch of other factors too. I fall into the latter camp of riders and would be lost without my Topeak Smarthead Digital Gauge (other pressure gauges are available).<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><h3>What should you ask them?</h3><p>Tire pressure is down to personal preference, of course. But, there are a good number of factors that will affect what that personal preference is. It’s good to be aware of what they are so you can adapt your pressures over the years to an ever-evolving bike setup.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/AASQ-submit-button.gif\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%22%20width%3D%22300%22%20height%3D%2250%22%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E\" alt=\"button to submit questions for bikerumor AASQ series\" width=\"300\" height=\"50\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/AASQ-submit-button.gif\"></a></p><p>Does wheel size matter? Does tire width matter? What about the tire casings? Does switching from a thin casing to a downhill casing warrant a change in tire pressure or not?</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17102539/WTB-VIGILANTE-TOUGH-HIGH-GRIP-MTB-TIRE-PRESSURE.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17102539/WTB-VIGILANTE-TOUGH-HIGH-GRIP-MTB-TIRE-PRESSURE.jpg\" alt=\"BEST TIRE PRESSURE WTB VIGILANTE 29ER 2.5&quot; TOUGH HIGH GRIP\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17102539/WTB-VIGILANTE-TOUGH-HIGH-GRIP-MTB-TIRE-PRESSURE.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/